<package format="3">

  <!-- ======================================================================
       PACKAGE IDENTITY
       ====================================================================== -->

  <name>line_follower</name>

  <!-- Semantic version: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH -->
  <version>0.0.1</version>

  <!-- One-line description shown in ros2 pkg list and documentation -->
  <description>
    Autonomous ROS 2 line-follower robot — Team VEGA Graduation Project 2026.

    This package implements a fully autonomous differential-drive robot that
    tracks a high-contrast line on a flat surface using a 5-element IR
    reflectance sensor array. The system integrates:

      - ATmega32 microcontroller running hard-real-time embedded firmware
      - HC-05 Bluetooth module providing a wireless UART bridge to the host PC
      - Five analogue IR sensors sampled via the ATmega32 10-bit ADC
      - Two optical wheel encoders (20 PPR) connected to INT0 / INT1
      - Dual DC motors driven through an L298N H-bridge at adjustable PWM duty
      - PID feedback controller (Kp=0.5, Kd=0.05) running at 50 Hz in ROS 2
      - Differential-drive kinematic model for dead-reckoning odometry

    ROS 2 Node Architecture:
      serial_comm_node        — UART/Bluetooth hardware gateway
      line_sensor_node        — IR weighted-centroid error computation
      line_controller_node    — PID control loop, publishes /cmd_vel
      motor_driver_node       — Twist-to-AVR command translation
      encoder_odometry_node   — Encoder-based pose estimation (/odom + TF)

    Key Topics:
      /ir_raw          (std_msgs/String)        — Raw IR binary frame S:XXXXX
      /line_error      (std_msgs/Float32)       — Normalised lateral error [-1,+1]
      /cmd_vel         (geometry_msgs/Twist)    — Velocity command
      /motor_cmd       (std_msgs/String)        — AVR motor command e.g. F7, L4
      /encoder_raw     (std_msgs/String)        — Cumulative tick counts E:L,R
      /odom            (nav_msgs/Odometry)      — Dead-reckoning pose estimate
  </description>

